    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Crack the<strong> eggs </strong>gently into the water and leave them for 3 min</p><p>Once done, gently transfer the <strong>eggs</strong> with a slotted spoon to<strong> </strong>kitchen paper or a clean tea-towel and season them with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>poached eggs</strong></p>",
